<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<Mod id="metropolis-ascendant" version="1"
	xmlns="ModInfo">
	<Properties>
		<Name>Metropolis Ascendant</Name>
		<Description>Metropolis Ascendant — one city per hemisphere. Make it the greatest the world has ever seen.
[N][N]Most of Civ VII rewards going wide. Metropolis Ascendant flips that: you build one towering city per hemisphere (one Homeland, one Distant Lands) and pour everything into making it extraordinary — a single, ever-denser metropolis that out-thinks, out-builds and out-cultures empires many times its size. A true tall overhaul: bonuses are at full strength only while you stay small, and switch off the moment you sprawl.
[N][N]KEY MECHANICS
[N]- Urban Population is power — your city's Urban Population (not rural) drives everything across three tiers (T1 / T2 / T3); specialists pay out full tile adjacency, so a dense city compounds fast.
[N]- Build through the trees — bonuses fan out across the tech and culture trees by victory domain: Science, Culture, Economy, or a dedicated Military lane.
[N]- One city, many towns — granary, mining, trade, fortress and resort benefits are all internalized into the single metropolis.
[N]- Suzerain layer — bonuses scale with how many city-states you lead: reach, resources and influence without founding another city.
[N]- Happiness pays off — keep the metropolis Joyous and it earns escalating Science and Culture per Urban Population (more while Ecstatic); specialists also cost less to maintain until the city is thriving.
[N]- Wonders &amp; Arcadia — concentrate Wonders and natural beauty in one city, a strength a sprawling AI empire can't match. Wonders make adjacent Buildings happier and beautify the land; discover a Natural Wonder and Arcadia opens up — Breathtaking rural tiles, Buildings beside Mountains, and even terraced Mountain peaks all become productive (scaling each Age). Arcadia also embraces the waters — rivers, lakes, the open sea and reefs each yield by type, you can work the open ocean in Exploration, and coastal cities gain a flat yield floor, so a water-heavy or island map is never a dead end.
[N]- Every victory stays open — if a packed metropolis has no open tile for a Modern victory Wonder, raise its Foundations over an existing district to complete it in place (only once you've earned the Wonder normally, never a shortcut), so all four victory paths stay reachable when you go tall.
[N]- A strict tall rule — every scaling bonus is full at exactly one settlement per hemisphere, and off at two or more.
[N]- Spans all three Ages: Antiquity, Exploration and Modern.
[N][N]Every bonus is described on the tech or civic node that unlocks it (mastery bonuses appear on the node's Mastery panel), so you always know what you are building toward.
[N][N]TIERS — Urban Population thresholds: 5 / 9 / 12 in Antiquity, 8 / 14 / 20 in Exploration, 10 / 16 / 24 in Modern. Every scaling bonus is full at exactly one settlement in a hemisphere and off at two or more (Towns count) — no partial taper. The specialist cap and safety nets fade more leniently and never revoke a placed specialist.
[N][N]Built and tested on Civilization VII 1.4.1. No DLC required. Experimental and actively tuned — feedback welcome.
[N][N]Built and developed using Claude Code.</Description>
		<Authors>Chris</Authors>
		<Package>Mod</Package>
		<AffectsSavedGames>1</AffectsSavedGames>
		<Version>1</Version>
		<LastUpdated>2026-06-22</LastUpdated>
	</Properties>

	<Dependencies>
		<Mod id="base-standard" title="LOC_MODULE_BASE_STANDARD_NAME"/>
	</Dependencies>
	<References>
		<Mod id="core" title="LOC_MODULE_CORE_NAME"/>
	</References>

	<ActionCriteria>
		<Criteria id="age-antiquity">
			<AgeInUse>AGE_ANTIQUITY</AgeInUse>
		</Criteria>
		<Criteria id="age-exploration">
			<AgeInUse>AGE_EXPLORATION</AgeInUse>
		</Criteria>
		<Criteria id="age-modern">
			<AgeInUse>AGE_MODERN</AgeInUse>
		</Criteria>
		<Criteria id="always">
			<AlwaysMet/>
		</Criteria>
	</ActionCriteria>

	<ActionGroups>
		<ActionGroup id="text-all" scope="game" criteria="always">
			<Properties>
				<LoadOrder>100</LoadOrder>
			</Properties>
			<Actions>
				<UpdateText>
					<Item>text/en_us/MetropolisAscendantText.xml</Item>
					<Item>text/en_us/MetropolisAscendantNotes.generated.xml</Item>
				</UpdateText>
			</Actions>
		</ActionGroup>

		<!-- Icons for the victory-wonder "Foundations" buildings (issue #1). Icons load via UpdateIcons (the icon DB),
		     globally (criteria="always") like the base game's art groups, not per-age. Reuses each target Wonder's blp icon. -->
		<ActionGroup id="recycle-icons" scope="game" criteria="always">
			<Actions>
				<UpdateIcons>
					<Item>data/icons/recycle-icons.xml</Item>
				</UpdateIcons>
			</Actions>
		</ActionGroup>

		<!-- Shared constructible-adjacency definitions in their OWN action group per age (LoadOrder 105, before the
		     modifiers at 110). ISOLATION: a data error here rolls back only this group, NOT the modifiers group, so a
		     bad row can't take the whole mod down (it did 2026-06-26: a wrong table name nuked the age group + crashed).
		     Kept per-age (not criteria="always") because the gameplay DB rebuilds each Age, so the rule must re-apply
		     per Age the same way the modifiers do. -->
		<ActionGroup id="antiquity-shared" scope="game" criteria="age-antiquity">
			<Properties>
				<LoadOrder>105</LoadOrder>
			</Properties>
			<Actions>
				<UpdateDatabase>
					<Item>data/shared/constructibles.xml</Item>
				</UpdateDatabase>
			</Actions>
		</ActionGroup>

		<ActionGroup id="antiquity" scope="game" criteria="age-antiquity">
			<Properties>
				<LoadOrder>110</LoadOrder>
			</Properties>
			<Actions>
				<UpdateDatabase>
					<Item>data/antiquity/modifiers.xml</Item>
					<Item>data/antiquity/traditions.xml</Item>
				</UpdateDatabase>
			</Actions>
		</ActionGroup>

		<ActionGroup id="exploration-shared" scope="game" criteria="age-exploration">
			<Properties>
				<LoadOrder>105</LoadOrder>
			</Properties>
			<Actions>
				<UpdateDatabase>
					<Item>data/shared/constructibles.xml</Item>
				</UpdateDatabase>
			</Actions>
		</ActionGroup>

		<ActionGroup id="exploration" scope="game" criteria="age-exploration">
			<Properties>
				<LoadOrder>110</LoadOrder>
			</Properties>
			<Actions>
				<UpdateDatabase>
					<Item>data/exploration/modifiers.xml</Item>
					<Item>data/exploration/traditions.xml</Item>
				</UpdateDatabase>
			</Actions>
		</ActionGroup>

		<ActionGroup id="modern-shared" scope="game" criteria="age-modern">
			<Properties>
				<LoadOrder>105</LoadOrder>
			</Properties>
			<Actions>
				<UpdateDatabase>
					<Item>data/shared/constructibles.xml</Item>
				</UpdateDatabase>
			</Actions>
		</ActionGroup>

		<ActionGroup id="modern" scope="game" criteria="age-modern">
			<Properties>
				<LoadOrder>110</LoadOrder>
			</Properties>
			<Actions>
				<UpdateDatabase>
					<Item>data/modern/modifiers.xml</Item>
					<Item>data/modern/traditions.xml</Item>
					<Item>data/modern/recycle.xml</Item>
				</UpdateDatabase>
			</Actions>
		</ActionGroup>
	</ActionGroups>
</Mod>
